The RASD Board of Education approved the reopen plan for the district on August 24, 2020. They also decided that the reopening will be in person grades PreK-6 and hybrid for grades 7-12.

If your family is choosing to enroll your children in distance learning, please complete the enrollment for distance learning for each child. It is a simple 2 minute form. The directions on the form will also provide some information on device pick up in preparation for the start of the year.

Otherwise, we will see most of you on September 8th!

post_text:
RASD Reopen Plan

Redwood Area School District will start with the ‚ÄúIn-Person‚Äù Learning Model for students Grades PreK-6

This means all students report M-F regular school hours.

Grades 7-12 will start in a hybrid model. Our numbers by county are low but to reopen the board has decided to proceed with caution and start with the hybrid at these grades.

This means students will report on alternating days with online instruction on the opposite days.

If numbers remain low and we continue to meet the state‚Äôs guidance for ‚Äúin person learning‚Äù, the district will assess and plan to move to that model on October 5, 2020.

Click below to view our Reopen Plan-3 Educational Model

What a great honor for Mr. Ellingworth.

Pidamayayapi to the LSIC, RASD Indian Parent Advisory Committee, district staff, school board, and community members who came out to (socially distance) celebrate RASD Superintendent Rick Ellingworth!!! An additional thank you to Councilwoman Grace for representing the community, Dane Nelson for performing an honor song, and to everyone for coming out in the rain!!!

A Redwood Falls resident had this wonderful idea. Thanks for sharing with the community....

Hello Redwood Falls Community!!! Thought this would be a great time to add some cheer to our community!

Each week print and color or draw and color a picture in keeping with the theme of the week. Then hang it in your window or somewhere on your house/yard to make it visible from the road.

Other families can drive or walk around to see how many pictures they can find while keeping our social distancing practices - maybe we will be able to share a little wave along the way! The more people that join, the more fun this will be!

We hope you have fun engaging in the scavenger hunt while maintaining social distancing!!

post_text:
Friday, 2/28: I was invited to take part in a Service Project opportunity with Miss Rohling's 4th Graders and Mrs. Mohr's Kindergartners.
The task: Paired up 4th graders with Kindergartners and I can not express to you how AMAZING this experience spoke to my heart. I entered Miss Rohling's classroom to a magical interaction between peers.....One glance around this classroom and these students were working together with amazing compassion, helping, teaching and working together--there were smiles, laughing and conversations happening with each other. Such a FANTASTIC project that will benefit so many kids and families in need. These 6 tie blankets will be donated to our local Southwest Health and Human Services Agency for kids and families in need. Way to go Miss Rohling's 4th Graders and Mrs. Mohr's Kindergarteners! #AlwaysTheCardinalWay

- Miss Jackie Ourada

The Redwood Area School Board is pleased to announce that Monday, January 27, 2020, at the regularly scheduled school board meeting, the Redwood Area School Board unanimously approved the employment of Becky Cselovszki to become the next Superintendent of the Redwood Area School District. She is scheduled to officially begin her duties as Superintendent of Schools July 1, 2020.

Ms. Cselovszki will replace current Superintendent Rick Ellingworth who will be retiring from the School District on June 30, 2020.

Read the full press release at: https://www.redwoodareaschools.com/page/hot_news/view/75

post_text: Friday, January 24th Reede Gray Elementary enjoyed a beautiful day sledding, celebrating our 2nd Quarter End of Quarter Party! These students chose to spend 50 of their earned Cardinal Coins to enjoy time sledding with their classmates! We enjoyed the giggles, screams, friendships and a few falls too! We are proud of all of our Reede Gray Students. *Be Respectful *Be Responsible *Be Safe #AlwaysTheCardinalWay

post_text: This 3-credit course includes the study of legal requirements of medications and medication administration, general information on medications, terminology, abbreviations, applicable terminology, and an overview of body systems and drug classifications related to medication administration while utilizing designated reference sources. Medications will be demonstrated in the classroom lab via the oral, ocular, respiratory, rectal, and topical routes. The students will study the ten major body systems and how they are involved in the pharmacology of drug use. Upon completion of the course, and meeting federal and state guidelines, the student will receive a Trained Medication Aide Certificate.

post_text: Miss Tews' 1st grade class played Mrs. Tews' first grade class at Cedar Mountain in a game of "Guess the Number" through Skype. Each class had a mystery number they picked and they took turns asking yes or no questions to figure out the mystery number.
